Parliament, Monday, 18 February 2019 – The Ad Hoc Committee to identify suitable candidates for the filling of vacancies at the Commission for Gender Equality (CGE) will tomorrow meet to shortlist candidates. In its previous meeting last month, the committee agreed that 24 candidates will be shortlisted. The committee will be considering candidates for shortlisting from a total number of 88 resumes that were submitted by applications. The committee will recommend names for filling eight vacancies. Details of the meeting: Date: Tuesday, 19 February 2019
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO IDENTIFY SUITABLE CANDIDATES FOR THE FILLING OF VACANCIES AT THE COMMISSION FOR GENDER EQUALITY, MS NONHLANHLA NCUBE-NDABA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa Landu
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8203 
